Can you move these comments to their own paragraphs, one each for Xtensa and CEVA and link to the github issue as well for the asymmetric quantization?

```cc 
#if !defined(XTENSA) && !defined(CEVA_BX1) && !defined(CEVA_SP500)
// TODO(b/170503075): xtensa kernels are less general than
// reference kernels and we ifdef out test cases that are
// currently known to fail.

// TODO(#44912): Remove uint8 support from the existing fully connected kernels and also remove the uint8 test cases. CEVA's fully connected implementation assumes weights_zero_point=0 as
// described in TFLite's quantization specification. Tests which use the deprecated asymmetric quantization for weights are ifdefed out.
```

